## Network comparison
This folder contains R script used to compare co-expression networks constructed from different networks.
The analyses focus on :
- comparing networks constructed from the combined host-symbiont dataset (S+M model) and single-species datasets (S model and M model)
- comparing networks from this study (multi-host genotypes x multi-symbiont genotypes dataset) with those reported in Riaz et al. (2025) (single-host genotype x single-symbiont genotype dataset)
These comparisons aim to evaluate how co-expression patterns vary under host and symbiont genetic variations.

## Input data
The following input files are required:
a) For Module eigengene correlations,
- "MEs_SM_Model.csv" Module eigengenes (MEs) for all libraries from the WGCNA with the S+M model
- "MEs_S_Model.csv" Module eigengenes (MEs) for all libraries from the WGCNA with the S model
- "MEs_M_Model.csv" Module eigengenes (MEs) for all libraries from the WGCNA with the M model

b) For overlapping between networks
To generate heatmaps showing gene overlap across networks:
- "Summary_Module_SM_Model.csv" Module assignment table for all genes from the WGCNA with the S+M model
- "Summary_Module_S_Model.csv" Module assignment table for all genes from the WGCNA with the S model
- "Summary_Module_M_Model.csv" Module assignment table for all genes from the WGCNA with the M model

c) For network comparison with Riaz et al. (2025)
Datasets from Riaz et al. (2025)
  - "suppl_file_S4.xlsx" Summed to gene/gene cluster counts for all Medicago (49,928) and Ensifer pangenome (12,107) genes. Also includes the locus_tag IDs for strains 1021and MABNR56, if in a gene cluster.
    (renamed as "Riaz_raw.xlsx" in these scripts)
  - "supple_file_S6 (pangenome-rhizobia module genes).csv" Module membership of Sinorhizobium meliloti pangenome gene groups in co-expression network.
  - "suppl_file_S8 (Plant module genes).csv" Module membership of Medicago truncatula gene co-expression network
These datasets are available in the Supporting Information of: https://www.pnas.org/doi/suppl/10.1073/pnas.2411831122

Datasets in this study
  - "WGCNA_Readcount.csv" 
  - "Summary_Module_SM_Model.csv"
  - "Summary_Module_S_Model.csv"
  - "Summary_Module_M_Model.csv"

d) References used to match Sinorhizobia protein IDs between datasets:
  - "GCF_002197065.1_ASM219706v1_genomic.gtf.gz" (available on https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/datasets/genome/GCF_002197065.1/)  (for this study)
  - "GCF_000006965.1_ASM696v1_genomic.gtf.gz" (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/datasets/genome/GCF_002197065.1/)  (for Riaz et al. (2025))

## Processing
The scripts in this folder perform the following steps:
a) Module eigengene correlations
  - S vs M networks
  - S+M vs S networks
  - S+M vs M networks
b) Module overlap between networks
  - Comparisons between S+M, S and M networks with generating heatmaps showing gene overlap between modules.
  - Comparisons with Riaz et al. (2025)
    - For Sinorhizobia networks
    - Riaz network vs S+M model
    - Riaz network vs S model
    - For Medicago networks
    - Riaz network vs S+M model
    - Riaz network vs M model
